<title>TUNISIA: Libya executes CIA-linked spies-radio.</title>
<headline>Libya executes CIA-linked spies-radio.</headline>
<dateline>TUNIS 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Libya executed on Thursday six senior officers and two civilians convicted of spying using equipment supplied by the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency, Libyan state-run radio reported.  </p>
<p>The radio, monitored in Tunis, said the six officers were executed by a firing squad while the two civilians were hanged.</p>
<p>Libya's Supreme Military Court sentenced the eight men to death on Wednesday for spying, using CIA equipment.</p>
<p>Washington denied any links and called the trial a &quot;propaganda ploy&quot;.</p>
